  <div class = "node">
    <p>Node js is a server environment that developed by Ryan Dahl on 2009. It runs on different platforms. It is a free and open source software provided for developers. Node js is a javascript-based that runs on V8 of javascript runtime environment. Node js executes a javascript and it provides different libraries and frameworks such as express, hapi, etc.</p>
    <h3>Features:</h3>
    <div class = "node">
      <ul>
        <li>Asynchronous and Event Driven</li>
        <li>Single Threaded but Highly Scalable - It can caters large request by providing services.</li>
        <li>Fast - Since it was built on V8 of javascript by chrome so the execution of the codes is faster.</li>
        <li>No Buffering - outputs the data in chunks</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <h3>Where to Use Node.js?</h3>
    <div class = "node">
      <p>You can use nodes on creating the following areas:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>I/O bound application</li>
        <li>Single page application</li>
        <li>JSON API’s based application</li>
        <li>Real-time applications</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <h3>Node Package Manager (NPM)</h3>
    <div class = "node">
      <p>NPM is a package manager of node that we use to install node js packages, modules, and frameworks. To install npm, use this command: <b>npm install</b>. That To install a module, use this command: <b>npm install [name_of_module]</b>. For example, “npm install express”. Once a module is installed, just use <b>require()</b> to use the module.</p>
